text.tspan: The max scope for a service
Pro tip: if you serve a service worker along with the Service-Worker-Allowed header, you can specify here
a list of max scopes for this worker.
After registering a service worker to controll a scope, each time a client in that scope request a resource from
The service worker for that scope enters the game and hijacks the request.
Through event.respondWIth() and passing a response object, the service worker can answer the client's request
with a custom response made out of different sources: the network, storage or its own code.
